 # Investigate zellij action dump-screen --pane-id for targeted cross-session queries
 
-
+Zellij 0.44 adds --pane-id flag to dump-screen and other actions, plus --session for cross-session targeting. Currently we use ZELLIJ_SESSION_NAME env var for session targeting and have no pane-level targeting.
+
+This could eliminate the ghost client requirement — if we can send-keys and dump-screen to a specific pane ID without needing a focused PTY client, the ghost-attach process becomes unnecessary.
+
+Key question: does --pane-id work without a ghost client attached? The ghost client exists because write-chars/dump-screen historically required a focused pane with a real PTY.
